reviews_data.review_text: I have had multiple negative experiences at the Harrisburg, NC library. Every time I try to use the computer there is a problem with my account.  They refuse to tell me what the problem is but somehow get it fixed after I ask for help about 3 times. Today I was there printing some things off for our adoption paperwork, and a library employee stood in front of the printer and stared at me the entire time I was using it (she was in my way and I literally had to reach around her to get my papers.  Why???) Then she disabled the printer so I couldn't use it, said "let me know if you need help" and walked away.  I have never felt so uncomfortable at a library and definitely will never return.
It was awesome! The customer service was superb! It has been awhile since I have been there and just reminded me while I always choose the Harrisburg location.
Amazing Staff and perfect for all ages

Very quiet and comfortable. The staff is relaxed in their demeanor but not in their professionalism!!!! Always have a wonder experience!!!! There is a great array of books for all ages especially for young mothers who want to have a great atmosphere in teaching their children how to read!!!!!

This library is hidden from those who don't want to educate their children. You will have a great time at this place. Also of note, there is a beautiful walkway outside for walking and a newly renovated/ extended park for the children!!!! This area is a great location.... Highly recommend!!!!
Quiet library. With a beautiful park across the street

EVERYTHING VERY NICE.
SERVICE AND ALL!!

Very nice and clean and well kept library.

One of the biggest issues, the workers/librarians themselves are loud nor do they enforce keeping the volume down or to keep it quiet.

Since they themselves are loud then can not enforce the rules of the library.

From the back of the library I can truly, truly, truly here everyone's conversation.(that's where I'm currently sitting)

If you coming here thinking that you will have a quiet place to study or work please throw that out the window.

Really and emphatically disappointed, I had such high hopes.
The food was wonderful. The management and staff was great.
Everything is nice but the bathroom was dirty
Absolutely an Amazing Environment for Children, Youth,  Adults.   Go Harrisburg Library!
Beautiful park! Lots of space for everyone to enjoy. Splash pad, playground and multiple covered seating areas!
Excellent library and facilities!!
Great library!

Worst library I have ever been to, and most likely I will never go back. This library is very loud. You can't study or try to read in a quiet atmosphere if you wanted to because of the ridiculous noise levels. The people who work there were not remotely friendly or helpful. I have been greeted considerably more warmly at Walmart than here! A patron was nicer to me and more helpful than the 4 staff members I encountered. Very disappointed with my experience and will look for another library to use.

Great library! Everyone that works there is always very nice and extremely helpful. It's a small library but they always have a really nice selection and do a good job of keeping it updated with new books and other media coming out.
There is a park and splash pad also at the location 0f Harrisburg.
My little friend and I had a great time. It was our 1st time and the people working there are very nice.
This library is far above and beyond in all categories. Staff is incredibly helpful, kind and professional. Clean, well organized and a great community spirit.

I’m here to study for college. They don’t have any private rooms or really a secluded area to study. The only desks they have are on the back wall, facing the wall. It’s such a small place I can hear the entire conversations the front desk ladies have lol. It’s not their fault- but the building itself is just so SMALL. I’ve been to libraries all across the country for work, and I held this one to a high standard. The customers in here are playing videos so it’s easy to hear- it’s just not a space for true quietness.

Overall, it is very clean. The ladies at the front seem nice. It looks like the community computers are up-to-date.
First time visiting this library and had a wonderful experience as the staffs are very friendly , Assist and helps signing up for the library card and everything.overall the process went smoothly.

Although the employees are friendly, there is consistent noise in the library each time I visit. It is very hard to study or concentrate even in the back of the space. Since it is a small space, there should be more enforcement of policies of quietness in the library, especially in the study areas of the library.

Loudest library there is!!! Employees are literally always screaming, which just sets the tone for parents and children to scream. Even in quiet designated areas staff and parents are yelling! Please make changes to lower volume, it is impossible to use the space as a library currently.
We came to study for exams and the employees were extremely loud and it was very hard to focus, I am very disappointed especially since library’s are supposed to be a place to focus, read and study.
Never visited this Library till today. I always go to the one downtown Concord. The fact that its a nice park right outside the library is pretty cool. Looks like fun for family

Comfortable for getting a little work or reading done. It has a nice children's area. Books are well organized and there is a good selection available on the shelves. Restrooms are clean and well maintained. They have a good selection of audiobooks on CD. Lots of different programs for kids to help encourage a love of reading. This is probably my favorite branch of the Cabarrus County Library System. plenty of parking available most of the time.

I’m a regular here, but I rarely spend much time in the library itself. Instead I use the fantastic online catalog to request books, audiobooks and DVD’s. This makes it super easy to pop by to pick up my items when I get the email notification that they’re ready - and they added a convenient curbside service in response to Covid. When they haven’t had what I was looking for, I’ve filled out an online request and more often than not the library has added the item to its catalog. As a bonus, this library is located right by the fantastic Harrisburg park. I love picking up my requested book, then walking over to find a quiet park bench to begin my new read!

Harrisburg branch Everyone’s nice and it’s a clean environment, but it’s the loudest and most distracting library I’ve ever been in. I came here to read/ study like everyone else. Not only are there parents and kids reading out loud, not even a whisper , but the workers are talking at normal volume instead of a whisper like most library’s encourage. While having phone conversations as well. And it’s constant chatter as well. No one seems to have the consideration of others of talking st a low volume realizing other people are here and  It doesn’t seem to stop. It was more distracting then a coffee shop. So back to the coffee shop it is.
Loudest library I’ve even been in….
Forgot how much I loved the library..

First time visiting here. Very nice library. I came to study but I cannot concentrate because the employees are talking so loud. Loudest library I have ever been too and I’m a library lover. I could understand if it were children but this is ridiculous. Has been going on for over and hour.
Comfortable!
The librarian went out of her way to find a book for me
Great and helpful staff.
One of the most valuable places in any community.
very accommodating.  staff super helpful!
Love the library! The librarians are knowledgeable and helpful here. Lots of great resources and programs.

Best place to go to spend some quality time with your kids or with yourself. The collection of books is not as big but they do make every effort to get you the books you are looking for. The staff are quite friendly and always willing to extra mile for any help.
Very attentive staff with awesome sales going on! I couldn’t have asked for better service and better prices for books!
The library is a great place but its closed on Sundays which is kind of annoying
plenty of activities great staff the head librarian is super fun yet peaceful and good for tutoring and clean
How awesome that you call, and after you select the option #1 to speak with someone it hangs up on you...GREAT WAY to keep your call volume down.....
Love this little library. They have good events like storytime for babies and toddlers, and they have a decent selection of books. The staff are very friendly and helpful.

This is a very small community library with a limited number of books on its shelves. That being said, I haven’t read them all yet. Computers are available to the public and I think it’s free for Cabarrus County residents. CDs, books, children’s, and teen area. There chess boards inside and rocking chairs outside. The staff is super helpful!
Nice library in Harrisburg located near the Harrisburg park. Lots of books for adults and a nice interactive section for kids of all ages

Love our library! Very clean and neat. Staff is always pleasant and helpful. Very quiet atmosphere with lots of cozy corners to relax and read. I am very thankful to have such a wonderful place to find books or order them in from other libraries. Beats buying them any day! Thanks staff for making my day so pleasant!!!! 💕 Read a book, take an adventure!!!!

Harrisburg Library is just a block off hiway 49 and tucked in a beautiful rural setting. It's small but there is plenty of comfortable seating to relax and browse through magazines or read.  The library also provides individual study cubes if you need to concentrate more than usual. The only downside to this particular Cabarrus County library is the noise level during the day. Don't be surprised if the quite is interrupted by crying infants, screaming children or talkative library assistances. I think the real problem is the interior design.  It's comprised of an open floorplan so all sound carries through the space.  I enjoy going there and will continue to do so, but just be forewarned about the potential sound levels.
Very helpful anf kind staff.
Merry Christmas
Very nice libary, fun events. Sometimes runs out of space for events so get there early
Lovely library with a cozy environment and friendly staff
Bello parque con una muy agradable biblioteca. Muchos eventos para niños y familia
Librarians were pleasant and very helpful

Library is great & helpful,

Early voting in 2016 is kind of weird with people getting in & out of line and groups seeming to isolate people who are there alone.  voting poles people oddly aggressive for some reason also.
Great library,with excellent staff

Had a most pleasant experience. We are in the process of moving to the area and needed to do research appliances for the new home. Everyone was helpful and found back issues of Consumer Reports for our use. They explained the process of obtaining a library card when we close on our home. I look forward to spending time in this library.

I love the Harrisburg Library. I go there at least once a week, and the staff is so nice and friendly. They know me since I'm there so often, and I just find it so refreshing from being so busy all the time.
Busy place. Very noisy. Staff are not exactly friendly or helpful.

Not at all helpful in finding the book "Son of Hamas". When I tried to get the contact information for the county library board she would not give it to me. Wasn't helpful in getting the book on inter-library loan either!
